This paper proposes a method for generating natural language sentences from probabilistic language models, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically evaluates the proposed method on an image captioning task, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes NLP, is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural network models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the performance using BLEU scores, which is a common evaluation metric in NLP and falls under cs.CL. Finally, the paper mentions a human evaluation, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves human subjects.
